sentence: Looking at the universe of stocks we cover at Dividend Channel, on 7/23/20, Coca-Cola Consolidated Inc (Symbol: COKE), Procter & Gamble Company (Symbol: PG), and Williams Sonoma Inc (Symbol: WSM) will all trade ex-dividend for their respective upcoming dividends.

Coca-Cola Consolidated Inc will pay its quarterly dividend of $0.25 on 8/7/20, Procter & Gamble Company will pay its quarterly dividend of $0.7907 on 8/17/20, and Williams Sonoma Inc will pay its quarterly dividend of $0.48 on 8/28/20.

As a percentage of COKE's recent stock price of $229.41, this dividend works out to approximately 0.11%, so look for shares of Coca-Cola Consolidated Inc to trade 0.11% lower — all else being equal — when COKE shares open for trading on 7/23/20.
Similarly, investors should look for PG to open 0.63% lower in price and for WSM to open 0.59% lower, all else being equal.
When an S&P 1500 component reaches 20 years of dividend increases, it becomes a contender to join the elite "Dividend Aristocrats" index.
Williams Sonoma Inc (Symbol: WSM) is a "future dividend aristocrats contender," with 14+ years of increases.
Below are dividend history charts for COKE, PG, and WSM, showing historical dividends prior to the most recent ones declared.
In general, dividends are not always predictable, following the ups and downs of company profits over time.
Therefore, a good first due diligence step in forming an expectation of annual yield going forward, is looking at the history above, for a sense of stability over time.
This can help in judging whether the most recent dividends from these companies are likely to continue.
If they do continue, the current estimated yields on annualized basis would be 0.44% for Coca-Cola Consolidated Inc, 2.52% for Procter & Gamble Company , and 2.34% for Williams Sonoma Inc.
In Tuesday trading, Coca-Cola Consolidated Inc shares are currently up about 1.1%, Procter & Gamble Company shares are up about 0.3%, and Williams Sonoma Inc shares are up about 0.4% on the day.
